  "body": "Hey, it looks like --opoose-dao-fork actually implements a hard fork by refusing to process blocks between 192000 and 192010 if they contain the wrong extradata.\n\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/5f55d95aea433ef97c48ae927835d833772350de/core/dao.go#L52-L54\n\nNodes running geth 1.4.10 will actually end up on a different fork than geth 1.4.9 if even one block in the range contains a spoofed extra-data\n",
